caption: Food is OK (in my opinion a bit greasy)..too expensive for what you eat and for the portions which are kind of small. Very nice atmosphere and very good service though!
(Translated by Google) I love Maite! Food is delicious  (Original) Me encanta Maite! La comida es deliciosa

This site is my first choice site.  Of all restaurants I know I prefere it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to this restaurant. everytime  I I need a good supper, this is the place that comes right away to my head. excellent and many types of  food and a large menu.well mannered team, and agreeable vibes. In addition to that, the pay is reasonable. I praise this spot with no hesitation.
Been going here on and off for about two years, there is lot of competition in the area, but today I had the bass fillets and they were incredible.
My favorite restaurant. Best place to spend your money on an immaculate meal. Also prettiest place. Duck Egg Arepa! LAMB!
Great ambience. Good food but small portions.
I would give this place 0 stars if that was a possibility.  I am appalled at the way the staff treats mothers and their children.
The place is wonderful and broad, the meals was yummy and the prices were very fair. quick, efficient service and very personal staff. I highly recommend this place.

The food is outrageously delicious. I’ve been multiple times and always leave satisfied and happy. The empanadas area must - perfectly crunchy and the meat filling never ceases to please even thought it changes based on what the chef finds at the market. The squid ink burrata is EVERYTHING. And whatever the vegetable side dish is - order it. The chef did a brown butter salsify once that RUINED my life because I have yet to find something comparable.  Oh and they have Txakolina on tap. which for those who know IS UGGGHHH amazing.
The best

Just ok. Food was pretty good, but the prices don't match the quality. Almost all mains were over $30. Food wasn't bad but it should have been priced $10 cheaper. For this price point, there are better options. Service was friendly.

This is probably my favorite restaurant in Brooklyn. Unique seasonal dishes, rich flavors, and such a warm inviting atmosphere. I used to live around the corner from it, and I miss it dearly since moving to LA. It is equally great for an intimate small plate date, as for a few drinks and snacks at the bar with friends, or an affordable late night burger and fries while reading or journaling. It is a gem. Get the Burrata with squid ink if it’s on the menu - you’ll be glad you tried it!
Seasonal, farm to table, thoughtful food. Don’t rush your meal. Order one of the excellent wines and always get the empanadas which change regularly. If they have the gnocchi on menu don’t miss it.
Me encanta! My fav plates are the chicharrón (always on point) the rib eye and the yuca fries

For price and quality this is maybe the best restaurant in NYC.  I've been to Michelin star restaurants all over the world and this is better than a lot of them.  I mean it's really incredible and I'd eat there everyday if I could!
The most underrated restaurant in the area. Spectacular food and wine. Bring binoculars to read the menu.

Absolutely delicious, everything I’ve tried. Amazing burger, yucca fries, cocktails... the list goes on. Used to dine-in BC (before corona) but ordering for take out is just as good! They accepted Venmo payments so even though I ordered online, I added an amazing strawberry rhubarb margarita when picking up. I heard a worker there say “no tips, that’s okay.” So I tipped double. ❤️

This place is my first choice restaurant.  Of all restaurants I know I like it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to visit this restaurant. Whenever  I I need a decent lunchon, this is the place that comes straightaway to my mind. good and all kinds of  food and a large list of dishes.courteous staff members, and great ambience. Not less important, the expence is good. I suggest this place with pleasure.

This site is my favorite place.  Of all restaurants I know I love it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to visit this restaurant. Whenever  I I need a delicious meal, this place comes right away to my head. splendid and varied  food and a large menu.trained staff, and nice mood. And very important, the bill is good. I praise this place with pleasure.
We had an awesome time in this place. We loved the extraordinary vibes and the food. The staff were very welcoming. I’m glad we finally decided to visit this spot.

I love this restaurant! They offer marvelous food, they have a rich menu, The chef in that place is a professional, I like very much tasting all their food. The food is consistently of high qualtity, the attitude towards the customers  is helpful. I often go to  this place and I not even once was disappointed. I recommend it with no hesitation.
Tried this spot already with a friend and I am obsessed since then. I liked the good atmosphere and delightful dishes and drinks. Fantastic work.
Food and drinks were excellent and the service was even better
Good food friendly staff. Though not inexpensive.
Coziest place ever. Always impeccable vibe.
Forever a favorite. Everything on the menu is absolutely delicious and the servers and overall restaurant have a great vibe. They also have the most decadent chocolate cake!
This place is the real deal. Got the duck empanadas and the burger, both mouthwatering.
Consistently stellar food.
Great staff and hands down the best burger I’ve had in Brooklyn.
Fancy-ish columbian food

This is my favorite neighborhood spot even though I don’t live in the neighborhood 😊. We come here all the time for the ambiance, the gnocchi and the empanadas. I could seriously eat the gnocchi every night. Staff is friendly and fun, cocktails are amazing, and I always leave happy!!!

Came here the other day with a party of 6 and we had a great time! we ordered about half the menu and the standouts were definitely the rib eye and burrata. The burger was also mouth watering. They also have great cocktails. service was on point. Cannot wait to go back! yum

I went here with my partner and had a fabulous meal. The pork belly was unreal and the gnocchi was melt in your mouth delicious. They have a great all natural wine selection. We sat at the bar and were well taken care of. Looking forward to going back and trying out more of the menu!

My wife and I went there for our anniversary dinner looking to have a very nice meal in a chill environment. The staff seated us at the table next to the restroom with a loud speaker while there were three huge communal tables open (those tables remained open the entire experience). We asked to move where they placed us in a high top next to the bar. We could barely fit so we eventually waited for seats at the bar. The menu seemed great..we went with the pork belly, mushrooms and gnocci. Pork belly was good but very big for two people since it's so fatty/oily. We were looking forward to the mushrooms (hoping for no something fresh), but they were underwhelming in flavor and again pretty oily. The gnocchi was a nice portion,  but they were in a bed of butter. Maybe we ordered the wrong items. The tastes all blended together and by the end we couldn't handle anymore fat without the flavor. For $150 on three items, we felt more taken advantage of rather than taken care of.

Went here last night and it was amazing! Basque and Colombian restaurant. The food changes from time to time so the server suggested that we take a picture of the menu and the drink menu to share with our party of 6 people since we were on the other end of the menu. We decided to order the following from the attached menu picture: (4) empanaditas (1) duck egg (2) Burrata (1) lasagna (1) pork belly (1) gnocchi with truffle (1) shishito peppers and (2) chocolate cakes (12) drinks and tip included, it came out to $407 for $68 per person. All REALLY good in my opinion but everyone loved the empanaditas. The duck egg was okay but our least favorite. Not bad for a Friday night dinner from 9PM - 11PM. Quick service and great environment.
Farm to table seasonal fare that's not crazy expensive and wonderfully prepared.
Love this place. Food is exceptionally great
Absolutely fantastic.
The best restaurant
They offer a fantastic range of delicious food. I enjoyed dining here. Employees are always welcoming, pricing is fair and the place is always clean.
This place is good! Good pricing, big portions and the employees are always nice.

Just had a couple of appetizers and beers that were very tasty. It is not cheap. No printed menu. You have to look at a giant chalkboard. Sat outside, next to corner where cars zoom by. Interesting to people watch in a neighborhood in transition. I found it surprising and offputting that they had to hold my driver's license for us to place our order. Nevertheless, I would try again.
Very much worth the visit for the unique menu of interesting, high quality dishes
(Translated by Google) Very vuena  (Original) Muy vuena
Best spot to have food when in a hurry. The service is fast, rates are reasonable, good atmosphere. Will come visit again
This spot is worth giving a shot. They have large portions for reasonable prices. Consistently well organized and with great vibes. Would recommend to others.
One of my go-to places to eat. excellent location, neat, and great service. I recommend this place!
Worst place ever dirty and bugs in my food never come here. Empanada contains dog food

A bit difficult to get to by transit. However a Uber ride away. The food and atmosphere is very laid back. Great menu! The staff is is very friendly. My only suggestion if you’re a party of four or more make reservations.
Ella's back. Reward your tastebuds. This place is sensually eloquent yet casual and well worth the price. Big big fan.
Really interesting menu and excellent customer service!

(Translated by Google) The attention is disgusting, where from the outside you can hear the verbal abuse of workers in the kitchen  (Original) La atención es un asco, donde desde afuera se puede escuchar el maltrato verbal a los trabajadores en la cocina
Excellent food, friendly employees, constantly  awesome vibes. They charge affordable rates and the food quality is excellent. 5 stars.
Unnecessarily expensive, the food is very small, not special and too greasy. Service is slow, bar needs to be clean, no need to comeback.

The service was fantastic, and the vibe inside was great. The food itself was good, but exorbitantly expensive. The food did not blow me away by any means, and was certainly not worth $100. My girlfriend had a #30 fish plate with morels -- the morels were delicious, the fish was just okay -- a tad overcooked and flavorless. I had a $24 burger and fries, which was good, but not $24 good. We probably won't be back

(Translated by Google) Comfortable bar with very good service. Nevertheless, the portion sizes unfortunately for the prices were not filling or sufficient.  (Original) Bequeme Bar mit sehr gutem Service. Dennoch waren die Portionsgrößen  leider für die Preise nicht sättigend bzw. ausreichend.
Loved it. Duck egg so good :)
Good food but not much if you're vegetarian or vegan. The squid ink and burrata are my favorite.

Have lived in Bushwick for 10 Years and DEEPLY ashamed to have never eaten here. Holy mother of God what an exceptional meal, top to tail. Lovely, warm, attentive service. Visually stunning food (squid ink reduction w/ mozz) Rack of lamb cooked perfectly, fried crab from Maryland (!!!!) Stupid good dessert, knowledgeable about after dinner drinks, perfect portions, v reasonably priced for the best meal I’ve had in years. GO HERE, it’s a gem.
Uuuugh, so good. Just go, order anything, all of it is to die for.
Drinks food and service, all on point

An out of the way eatery with a relaxed vibe, great for first dates, second dates, and date one-hundred. The chef and manager are fantastic - service is sharp, and dishes are full of passion. Check out their surprising bourbon selection.
Just finished dinner here with my partner. We loved the pork belly. The marcilla sausage arepita was delicious. The gnocchi were very soft. We will have to try the rotating menu again sometime!
Take care with the food. Bad cleaning for the ingredients, I found garbage in my food and the don’t apologize. Bad experience, expensive and bad service.

A wonderful and cozy bistro-like environment, which provides consistently excellent well-portioned and savory dishes, reflecting Colombian but also Basque influences. Never over the top. Always well prepared. Well worth a visit.

The menu is new every time you go. It can change throughout the night. The plates are meant to be shared, everything was tasty. We had some roasted peppers and a few other plates that didn't disapoint
Expensive but exquisite dishes, great cocktails and wine and very friendly service.

I have spent more money in one evening here then I care to admit, but it can't be helped. The food and cocktails were just too good, so of course I had to order multiple. Very good farm-to-table restaurant with a nice atmosphere.
The food was delicious! My boyfriend and I both enjoyed everything we got and will defiantly go back.

This is the best destination for a gastronomic experience in Bushwick. The food is innovative and truly delicious, with seasonal ingredients and an interesting take on Basque and Columbian cooking. The place is extremely welcoming and is perfect for big groups as they have many large tables. Their small selection of wine (natural!!) and the cocktails are also perfect. We love this place!

Incredible farm to table restaurant, the menu is only written on the wall and changes daily based on the season. I’ve been several times and every dish is complex and exciting to eat! Each dish is like the story of two people and how they exist together. Maite challenges your palate and that’s the best thing about their food, don’t worry if you don’t know what your ordering, trust, they know what their doing. For 2 people I’d recommend 3 or 4 dishes.
Food was outstanding.  Great night out.
Great!all around!!
The pork belly was crispy and delicious.  The gnocchi is a stand out.  The duck ragu was nicely done with a great sauce.
I wish i could afford to eat here once a week.  Love it.
(Translated by Google) Good place to hang out  (Original) Buen lugar para pasar el rato
Best tapas ✋✋ down
Great food and services. A bit pricey,  but worth the splurge!😋
Small menu, unique, and high quality food
Best meal I’ve had in a while
Always so beautifully delicious and amazing.
Great new idea in Columbian food... beautiful place...

This place is great!  I came here with a group of girlfriends and we had the empanadas, lamp chops, duck pasta and burger...all were amazing!  Great cocktails and atmosphere too, actually went back the next night!

(Translated by Google) Delicious and original food, kind attention and a very nice place. Highly recommended.  (Original) Deliciosa y original comida, amable atención y un sitio muy agradable. Altamente recomendable.
Great food and better atmosphere. All good except soggy fries. Delicious pork belly but please drain the oil. Delicious gnocchi and tasty arepa.

This place is priced high. We paid $55 for a ribeye in Bushwick. I understand farm to table but there better priced ones all through Brooklyn. I paid $58 for Prime USDA ribeye at Morton's with more meat and better price point.
Colombian food, fresh menu daily, full bar.
iberian cider, cheddar and leeks

I kept it simple.  Just a burger and fries, please.  They were really good.  The fries portion was huge and half of it came home with me.  There are a lot of exotic foods on the menu, many of which I had not heard of.  Staff is attentive without being overbearing.

Love this neighborhood gem! Friendly atmosphere and the food is fantastic! Favorites definitely are the burger with the crispy egg and the empanaditas with the spicy aji sauce to start. Also they have a great natural wine selection which many restaurants don't offer.
I had such a great experience at Maite! The gnocchi and the burger were so delicious! Great wine selection too. Loved the vibe here. Can't wait to go back!

My niece went here this weekend and I was very impressed with the atmosphere and especially the food. We ordered the rack of lamb, pork belly, seasonal salad, empanadas and a side of ramps. To drink we ordered a beautiful bottle of Cinsault. Everything was wonderful and great value! We look forward to coming back soon. Thank you Maite!

Cute place but over priced and VERY disappointing food ! Will bot go back ! 5 of us and all disppointed. Got served a 23 usd deep fried pork belley ( mainly fat) with not even a leaf of salad to garnish. The risotto was way over cooked and too cheesy and the meat of the burgers hard and simply bad. We had to return a glass of wine because of some cork in it and the glass was filthy . Yes atmosphere was nice but simply not enough if you also want decent food . It s A big NO !
Never again
One of the best restaurants in the hood!!
Extremely tasty sharing dishes. It was nice having something different to eat. My wife and daughter and I all enjoyed the dishes we chose
Best fries ever!! But really, their food is fantastic - you have to also get the collard greens and their shrimp risotto. So good!
Awesome spot, I love the decor
Omg the Burgers though!!!

Wow, what can I say. I just love this place! I came here to celebrate my birthday and as usual the food never disappoints. The chicharrón is out of this world and the burger and steak is mouthwatering. The wine is delicious as are the cocktails. The staff are all so nice and always make us feel at home. Such a special place....I can’t wait to come back for more!

Interesting. However certain aesthetics clash with dining experience like the dim lighting while having to read a menu on a wall barely visible. This only affected first impressions and initial  comfort. But for what they miss in intial experience they deliver ridiculously in  the food which is what matters ultimately. Everything especially burger, the sea food dishes, the pasta dishes, were absolutely delightful.
Precisely and smartly prepared dishes. For example, the cheese flan had a lovely blueberry liqueur that actually brought a scent of blueberry and a fine, almost crispy caramelized bottom.

Great service and delicious farm to table food. We got a bottle of wine, a few drinks, a few apps, and two entrées. It came out to a very reasonable $200 considering all the alcohol we had. Most entrees are under $20 and most appetizers are around the $10 mark. Would definitely come again.
Eat all the things
Amazing restaurant! Delicious fresh food and great chill atmosphere, can’t wait to go back!
i visited maite over new years the lamb was fantastic as was the steak and gnocchi! wow amazing food prepared with love! my favorite cocktail was the kiko, cava with pickled bourbon grapes. amazing!
Always amazing delicious food. Great staff and wine.

Very delicious food! It's a bit silly that they don't print their menus so you have to go look at the chalkboard but whatever you order will be amazing. I think we had a duck egg arepa and it was incredible!

The location was freezing. They had overpriced and tiny cocktails which weren't even poured to the top. No paper menus so you had to walk up to this giant chalkboard menu and stand there like an idiot. There were only 2 tables with people and the waiter brought us over the wrong drinks. The food was incredible. Everything else was sub par
Great food and very friendly service. I always recommend as a neighborhood joint.

This place is a good place but its a hit or miss. I see this place closed more than I see it open. Granted I'm in the neighborhood a lot. Yet really only open for Dinner ? I gave 4 stars because of the drinks. The food is an acquired taste not for everyone check the menu first.  A lot of people like this place. I'm not that much of an explorer with my taste buds.

Went here a couple years ago with a girlfriend, had one of the best meals of my life. Incredible quality of ingredients and care in the service and prep. We ordered many dishes and shared them all, the empanada was a godly masterpiece in perfect form and flavor. Tremendously cozy ambience and excellent, knowledgeable staff.

Need to edit my post because this place is out of this world. The prices are a bit higher than usual in the area but trust me, this is one of the best places I have eaten in the world. We dove into the menu and ordered the Burrata Negra, Mushroom with Egg Yolk, Gnochi with Red Scallions and the Rib Eye with Arepas and Anchovy Butter. All worth every penny! The cocktails are also worthy of mention, can't go wrong with any to be honest. Can't wait to go back and try everything on the menu and get the rip eye again...

In terms of ambience it's one of the better restaurants in the area. Great place to go in a group. However, the portions are small and overpriced. Everything was a tad too salty, with most of the sauces overpowering the flavor of the base ingredients.
Mediocre all around

Pricey, delicious, farm-to-table restaurant in a quieter part of Bushwick, Maite would be a perfect anniversary or splurge date spot. The staff is warm, knowledgeable, and quick with recommendations. Drinks were solid (delicious wild strawberry margarita), but not mind blowing.
Really great small plates

The menu is a collection of small plates meant to be shared. They have some exotic choices, like cheese in a squid ink sauce. Very pricey, and the portions are tiny. For 4 bites of, say, eggplant and shrimp, you pay about $20. The menu is only on a blackboard on the wall - no paper menus. Challenging for anyone with eyesight worse than 20/20.
Super cool Bushwick eatery. Tasty empanaditas with the best aji. Awesome selection of wines. Menu rotates often to keep it seasonal. Love!!
Amazing food & service! Don't forget to order the Wagyu Rib Eye and the empanaditas!

I came here for dinner the other night - great vibe, variance of food quality.  I shared orders of bread, pork belly, lamb chop, and empanaditas.  Empanaditas: very good! The meat inside was delicious!  Pork belly: pretty good, but SO overpriced for the quantity.  Lamb chop: not the best, in my opinion, but my partner seemed to like it. Also overpriced.  Bread: the bread was actually super good, especially with their special butter spread over.  With that said, we ordered about $50 of food, but left still slightly hungry. Likely won't come again.
Excellent food !! ❤️
Tasty food in a cool spot. Felt the food was a little on the pricier side for what we got.

This place is awesome. Awesome beer selection, had an illuminating basque cider. Delicious food-- lots of care put into the details. Had a tongue arepa which blew my mind. This place is done right by people who know good : go there and learn to taste anew.
Food and service was excellent. The dinners are a bit expensive, but well worth it.
Decent food, prices a little too expensive for what it is. The basket of fries might have actually been the best thing we ate...Although my Hot Toddy drink was well done.
An amazing array of dishes! I love starting with the empanaditas - they change the contents every week or so.
Delicious food and drinks and very cozy and quiet. Weird ordering experience with the only menu being poorly labeled on a giant blackboard far from some of the tables, but the food makes up for it.
Easily my favorite local restaurant. The gnocchi is light years beyond other places and the other dish's are just so good.

Entrées were delicious (the rabbit and the fluke), but we had to send two of the three drinks we ordered back to the bar. Also, every item on the menu is about $3 more than it should be. Don't go if you're on a tight budget (it came out to about $50 per person, and we were still hungry); otherwise, it's worth a shot for the food alone.
Lovely atmosphere, beautiful restaurant. Gnocchi was delicious and pork belly was off the chain!
Good place, a bit pricey though, but servise is ggood and food is good
My favorite spot for dinner in Bushwick. The gnocchi is hands down the greatest I've ever had, anywhere, ever.

I love the warm friendly feeling of the place and there is always a nice variety of drinks to choose from. The food is to die for and every time I go I must have the hand made empanadas and gnocchi. I mix it up when it comes to the entree, depending on what the special is. The whole experience is fulfilling. ❤️
Haven't tried much else other than desert but it's a great one!

Excellent staff and charming atmosphere combine with a rustic menu.  Though it does run a little cheese heavy,  so if one of you is lactose intolerant, you might go down the street.  Those who stay will be treated to perfectly cooked pork belly,  insufferably good gnocchi and a burger that you will write home to dad about
Good and cozy, I had to have my friend explain what most of the things on the menu were, but it was cute
Food was delicious, but overpriced. Not sure if I could justify how much I paid for the steak.

The food is really good but they need menus. The menu is written on a poorly lit wall and the writing is squished together. I saw some customers squinting to see the menu and I had to take a pic so I can read it and not stand in the middle of the restaurant like a jack ass. It's a stupid idea. I work in restaurants and i just left work and didn't want to cook after working a busy brunch and i think the chef in any restaurant would understand. I should have listen to my husband and had dinner at work but I wanted to try something new but in my restaurant our shrimp dish comes with past and veggies. Our shrimp r regular size but it will fill u up. Unlike their food. I got 3 jumbo large shrimp and very little sautéed greens and it was very pricy. If I ordered an appetizer I can understand the mix up but we wouldn't have had that if they had actual menus that said appetizer and entrees. And its only a few cents for potato's, pasta or a rice. I paid $15 for 3 very large and very good but not very worth the money shrimp. I wanted a meal they gave me an appitizer.
Amazing! Unreal! Go, enjoy, then go again! ... Then again! :)
The food was tasty but extremely expensive for what it is. I enjoyed my dinner but I simply don't make enough money to go back frequently. Maybe one day!
Awesome & inventive Latin fusion food, good prices, romantic decor & OK but friendly service

This staff will serve you excellent food and drink with a friendly nonchalance. Though you may be eating one of the finest burgers your likely to put in your mouth, it will not be served to you with pretense.

A wonderful new restaurant offering delicious food and a friendly, warm atmosphere. Fresh, local ingredients highlight an eclectic menu - chef/owner Ella Schmidt seems equally adept with meat, fish and pasta and with marrying European and American influences. The risotto-stuffed squid, pork ribs, empanditas and burger were all delicious.
